The warrima takes something like a rope out of his stomach(!), and climbs up to waijong to have an interview with the wagai. On his return, if the man is to recover, he says 'Your wagai has come back and you will soon be well', but if he is to die, he says 'I could not get your wagai.' The wagai are also the spirits consulted when anyone dies suddenly, discover by whose means the death was brought about.'
